	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Okay, Here's two reason.
<br />
<br />
<br />4K ROM's are a waste and just adding 4K to that (Like every NES game ever released) lets you do alot more with graphics and backgrounds.
<br />
<br />8K is the minimum standard. Even the simplest NROM games use 8KB graphics. (Searching for games under 16KB in size yields one result, galaxian clone that uses 8KB PRG and 8KB CHR, still too much)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


