	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />neilbaldwin, yes, it should be easy. I could make a function which will puts the data as .db's into the Windows clipboard, it is ok, or you need file export?
<br />
<br />3gengames, you giving me not the information I need. Of course I know that the CHR ROM banks are 8K. I use NESASM, which allows me to include arbitrary set of data in a bank. So I just incbin two 4K *.chr files to fill a CHR ROM bank, and there is no waste, you just have two *.chr files instead of one. I assume that more than one page on a screen is a rare case (requires tricks to switch pages mid-screen), and I don't plan to support these cases, that's why 4K files.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


